# Consumer at `root//leak_destination/consumer:c` -- in the
# `root//leak_destination/...` patch the leaky_target's `visibility =`
# list explicitly grants. WITHOUT the intersection cap, this dep would
# succeed (target's visibility allows it). WITH the cap (set by
# `intersect/PACKAGE`), the consumer must ALSO be in `root//intersect/`
# -- which it is not -- so the cap blocks the dep. This is the test
# that proves the cap actively narrows a non-PUBLIC visibility list.
stub(
    name = "c",
    deps = ["root//intersect/leaky_target:t"],
)
